It was perhaps the most important of Spanish colonial America, is characterized by its originality and its great value and the artistic result of the confluence of two powerful currents: the Western artistic tradition, on the one hand, and the eagerness of Indian painters and mestizos of expressing their reality and their vision of the world, on the other. In general, the works are not signed, since the pre-colonial tradition that artistic expressions belong to the community is followed. Our picture - dating. Circa 1680.
